<br>
If the mob stays up for over 24 hours, it goes FFA. What does this do? It gives the guild in rotation their turn, if they can't make it it gives everyone a chance to get an extra mob.<br>
Hell, let's say KT is up and it's BoTS turn, some tragedy happens and they leave it up, next day it goes FFA. Let's say Tindi is next in rotation.<br>
<br>
Since KT is FFA from BoTS leaving it up, then Tindi kills KT, patch day KT spawns, guess what? It's Tindi's turn again.<br>
<br>
That is the price you pay for breaking the 24 hour thing, you stand the chance of losing the mob.<br>
<br>
This would maximize the mobs coming in and out and would offer some people a chance at mobs they would have to wait on otherwise.<br>
<br>
Also, I would say that if guild XYZ has begun to pull or attempt the mob before the 24 hours, then the mob is theirs per rotation, and they can continue to attempt until they give up (at which time the mob goes to next in line) or they kill it. <p>Pictures are worth a thousand words. Someone asked me to shutup so I took down my picture. Now my posts are all 1000 words less.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugalladel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galladel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wog</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(12/4/01 9:13:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=905.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rotation Penalties</span><hr size=1>      The only problem with the mob going FFA after 24 hours is that it gives guilds with peak player times that are earlier (due to time zone/occupation/etc) than others an advantage.<br>
<br>
     If I were a GM of a guild who's prime time was 1pm to 9pm central, and I were trying to maximize kills after a patch, I'd leave one or two rotation mobs up and chase others. Knowing my guild is going to be able to set up 6 hours ahead of the ones who's main force works 9-5 and lives in the States, and they'll honor the agreement and leave the mob up for me.<br>
<br>
    Personally, I agree with that after 24 hours it passes to the next guild.  Exceptions being if per RTA you cannot zone into fear; there's an uniamous agreement by all members on the rotation; server connectivity and stability are giving you a rogering.<br>
<br>
       (note : not pointing fingers, pure speculation) <br>
