<br>
Why not a rule that states something like this:<br>
<br>
From the moment the mob spawns (or you are notified that the prior guild is passing) you have 24 hours to kill that mob or pass to the next guild. After 24 hours the mob automatically passes to the next guild.<br>
<br>
------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I like that the best. Ya know, you people are reading WAY to much into a game... lol. Yes, the kills are nice, yes the kills are fun, but... why even bother trying to justify a system that has such deep rooted issues? lol   Now, by all means, I am not knocking the efforts to avoid conflict in game... now that I know a little more about how the RTA works, I can see why it was put into effect. However, there are a certain few things that should be cut and dry... this is one of those issues. If your guild can't make the mob kill in 24 hours (plus or minus a few minutes, at most 30) then the mob gets passed on. Now, say someone blatently goes over the limit? Well, they loose thier next rotation. <br>
<br>
