<br>
________________________________<br>
I. From the moment the mob spawns (or you are notified that the prior guild is passing) you have 24 hours to kill that mob or pass to the next guild in the rotation. After 24 hours the mob automatically passes to the next guild on the rotation.<br>
<br>
II. Guilds are free to do with their scheduled spawn turn as they wish.  Meaning, guilds can swap them, or give them as gifts to other guilds, provided that such guild assuming your turn meets with the rules in I above.  For example, if you swap turns and the guild who takes your spot fails to kill the mob by the alloted 24 hours and the mob is still up, it is considered a pass and the next guild in the rot is up.<br>
<br>
III.  Any guild who's turn it is that fails to abide by the rules in I above, say by jumping turns or killing on the 25th hour, automatically loses the next turn it has in the rotation.<br>
_________________________________<br>
<br>
This is just my general take for the guild leaders to look at.  Do with it as you wish. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usss0rn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sss0rn</A> at: 12/11/01 9:41:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uemilsinclair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emil Sinclair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blood of the Spider</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(12/11/01 10:11:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=905.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: bad</span><hr size=1> swapping only exists in a 2 guild rotation;<br>
